Android Studio & GitHub - Lesson 1 Setup (NEW) by Will Willis
----------------------------------------------------------
Linux
    Install Git
        sudo apt install git (or aptitude)

Android Studio
    File->Close Project (to get "Configure" screen up)
    Configure->Settings
    Version Control->Git
    Fill in "Path to Executable" - needed? automatic?
        Ensure that "SSH executable" is "Build-in"
        Click "Test"
           Ensure Git executed successfully
    Android Studio menu
        "VCS"->"Git"
            Host: "github.com"
            Login: ?
            Password: ?
            Auth Type: "Password"
            Click "Test"
                Verify "Success"

Android Studio & Gitub - Lesson 2 Import & Push (NEW) by Will Willis
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Android Studio menu
    "VCS"
    "Share project on GitHub"
        Fill in "New Repository Name" - created on GitHub
            Click "Share"
    Select "app" - checks sub-directories
        Leave "Initial commit" for commit message.
        Click "OK" - may take a few minutes
            Ensure Success message
    Should be on github at this point

To use: Android Studio bar
    Puch & Pull Icons for changes
